item.title: ICE just tried to deport this woman, but there was just one problem — she was Native American.
item.description:
You read that right: Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) — the agency supposedly tasked with deporting undocumented immigrants — just tried to deport an Indigenous woman whose ancestors have been here for thousands of years. Leticia Jacobo, a 24-year-old member of Arizona’s Salt River Pima-Maricopa Indian Community, was born in Phoenix — but that didn’t stop ICE from trying to ship her “back” to a country she doesn’t even belong to.
Let that sink in: the United States government almost deported an Indigenous woman from her own country. It’s time to abolish this corrupt and incompetent agency that can’t even tell the difference between an immigrant and an Indigenous citizen.

item.title: trolling is ai art
item.description: I actually use some AI art in places where it doesn't matter. Like I have Telegram groups for friends and family, and I get AI to make me cute little badges with glowy text. That's a perfect use of AI. They're not all quite consistent, but close enough, and it looks nice. Do I use AI on my websites? Not for my clients, hell no. On most of my personal sites, nah. I did use a Ghibli-style filter on some of my photography for one site, and I like it, but I can understand if others hate it. I'm just saying - I think there's a place for it, but that place is relatively rare. And certainly not in any professional use - except to generate placeholders with the clear understanding that they MUST be replaced and are JUST placeholders.

These visas can only be used when the applicant certifies that they can't find US workers to fill the jobs. Of course, we should believe him because these are highly skilled positions that take years of education and training to master, like hotel housekeepers, servers, lawn mowers, etc. "...the Trump Organization’s visa requests increased from 121 in 2021 to 184 in 2025, according to Forbes.
